<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-64-0766 </DOCNO><TEXT>After almost forty years, the question of nuclearism is becoming a publicissue. By &quot;nuclearism&quot; is meant the knowledge and technical managementof nuclear weaponry, a politics that takes their possible use for granted,and a &quot;religious&quot; sense that possession of nuclear weapons is the foundationof national security. There are many difficulties surrounding a considerationof nuclearism. The author discusses several of these.</TEXT></DOC>